Anya Creightney program manager

00:01:43.220 --> 00:01:45.490
and the Poetry and
Literature Center,

00:01:45.490 --> 00:01:47.830
I'd like to share a
quote and a reference

00:01:47.830 --> 00:01:50.960
to another work authored
by Cristina Rivera Garza.

00:01:50.960 --> 00:01:55.520
It's called "The
Unusual Manifesto".

00:01:55.520 --> 00:01:58.390
"Writing is a community-making
practice.

00:01:58.390 --> 00:02:02.160
If we write, we write
with others, inescapably.

00:02:02.160 --> 00:02:05.570
If we write, we write about
others, even when we write

00:02:05.570 --> 00:02:08.550
about ourselves in small
diaries that remain hidden

00:02:08.550 --> 00:02:10.020
and locked in drawers.

00:02:10.020 --> 00:02:13.520
Constantly borrowing from the
language we share, with entire

00:02:13.520 --> 00:02:16.050
and varied communities at once.

00:02:16.050 --> 00:02:20.890
When we write, we acquire
debt, a real material debt,

00:02:20.890 --> 00:02:22.670
with the practitioners
of such languages.

00:02:22.670 --> 00:02:25.310
It is an immense debt.

00:02:25.310 --> 00:02:27.450
The same could be said
about library work,

00:02:27.450 --> 00:02:30.130
and its likely translation.

00:02:30.130 --> 00:02:32.150
It is a community
making practice,

00:02:32.150 --> 00:02:36.550
which we do with others,
describing and sharing writing,

00:02:36.550 --> 00:02:39.580
always borrowing and
continually building

00:02:39.580 --> 00:02:41.730
on an already enormous debt".

00:02:41.730 --> 00:02:45.530
Thank you all for being part of
this community today and know

00:02:45.530 --> 00:02:47.980
that you are welcome in
the Hispanic Division.

